How do you align a row of divs to the right using flex in css?  Show me an example.
Sure, here's an example code snippet that will center align a row of 3 div elements horizontally (assuming they have class names "col-md-4"):

    .row {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .col-md-4 {
        flex-basis: 33.33%; /* calculated as 1/3 of the row width */ 
     }

In this example, we use a `div` element with class "row" to create a flex container for our 3 child div elements (with classes "col-md-4"). We then set its display property to "flex", and align-items: center. Finally, each of the three children have their own width specified using CSS Flexbox's flexible units (`flex-basis`).
